Message:
make: Support spaces in filenames in bundle names.

Part 1. All changes in this CL are covered by tests, leaving out any single
thing makes one of the tests in the tests/mac directory fail.

Changes:

* Replace ' ' with '\ ' for some makefile rules, assert neither name nor
  dependency contains a space in the other cases. I looked at all callers
  of WriteDoCmd() and WriteMakeRule().

* In particular, self.output and self.output_binary always have '\ ' for spaces

* Quote a few things:
+ cmd_link: For app bundles with spaces (e.g. "chromium helper") 
+ cmd_solink: For framework bundles with spaces (e.g. "chromium framework") 

* Schwartz transform the make "dir" function to handle spaces

* I couldn't find a way to let the make functions "wildcard" et al work with
  spaces. They're used only for .d file handling, so .d filenames have their
  spaces replaced with a non-space character. That's true for the
  dependencies checked by "command_changed" as well.

Mac/ninja: Add support for prefix headers.

I tried 3 approaches:

1. extra_cflags on cc command, separate pch command
   ( http://codereview.chromium.org/9065001 )
2. override cflags per rule to add -include for source files and -x for gch files
   ( http://codereview.chromium.org/9028003 )
3. have a base_cflags with normal flags, set cflags to $base_cflags -include,
   override it with $base_cflags -x for gch files
    ( http://codereview.chromium.org/9064001/ )

1 is messy but fast. 2 is cleaner but a lot slower (due to cflags per .o file). 3 is cleanish and fast.

1 is what the make generator is doing. I wanted to do something like 2 but couldn't figure out
how to convince make's variable scoping to do that.

3 requires not passing cflags_cc to objcxx invocations (else it gets two -includes),
so instead set cflags_mm to $cflags_cc.

This change implements the general idea of 3., but with the extra_cflags (called cflags_pch) from 1.
Also enable the first test in test/mac for ninja!

Loosely based on a patch from Jeremy Apthorp <jeremya@chromium.org> (approach 1.)

make/mac: Delay space escaping until write time.

self.output and self.output_binary used to contain escaped spaces. Instead,
let WriteMakeRule() escape spaces, WriteDoCmd() now does so by transitivity.
Manually escape spaces in every WriteLn() call.

This gets rid of the awkward escape->unescape in WriteXcodeEnv() and allows
sharing that code with the ninja generator.

utils:  Add BasicAuthAction.

BasicAuthAction is an action for HTTP Basic Authentication and it will
be used to authenticate users to access Git or SVN repository.

utils: Fix BasicAuthAction's BASE64Decoder warning

Use org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64 instead of sun.misc.BASE64Decoder.
utils: Fix basicauth which works incorrectly.

GitApp: Allow anonymous access to git repository.

And refactor GitApp.java.

Fixed on #316

* Method may fail to clean up stream or resource
* Class defines field that masks a superclass field
* Reliance on default encoding
* Removed Unused field
* Removed unused variable
* Format string should use %n rather than \n
* Compare String value with equals() rather then ==
* Method names should start with a lower case letter
* Field isn't final but should be
* Suspicious reference comparison
* Primitive value is boxed then unboxed to perform primitive coercion
* Comparison of String parameter using == or !=
* Possible null pointer dereference in method on exception path
* Redundant nullcheck of value known to be non-null

auth: Fix authorization works incorrectly.

After visiting a public repository via web browser, authorization have
worked incorrectly because BasicAuthAction set a cookie for an anonymous
user. This patch prevents to set a cookie for an anonymous user.
auth: Remove duplication by using addUserInfoToSession.

user: UserApp.isRememberMe is deleted, use UserApp.currentUser

  session data

  UserApp.authenticateWithPlainPassword does not return null anymore
- add tests

AccessControl: Support to refuse anonymous access

If application.allowsAnonymousAccess configuration is true,
AccessControl refues any anonymous access.

Remove BasicAuthAction.isAnonymousSupported which is not necessary
anymore because new application.allowsAnonymousAccess and AccessControl
can cover the case of flase BasicAuthAction.isAnonymousSupported.

Upgrade Play from 2.2.6 to 2.3.6

* Upgrade sbt from 0.13.0 to 0.13.5.
* Upgrade jsmessages from 1.6.1 to 1.6.2.
* Downgrade play-2-mail from 1.0.0 to 0.9.1.
* Split project/Build.scala into build.sbt and
  project/BuildConfig.scala.
* Introduce sbt-less.
* Introduce sbt-twirl, the new template engine for PlayFramework, and
  fix compile errors caused by it.
    * Import scala.collection.JavaConversions._ for conversion between
      Java and Scala collections.
    * Import java.lang_ and java.util._ to use java types.
    * Use implicitJavaLang imported from play.core.j.PlayMagicForJava._
      instead of lang.
    * Use requestHeader imported from play.core.j.PlayMagicForJava._
      instead of request.
    * Specify play.data.Form in full qualified name to avoid conflict
      with play.api.data.Form.
    * Fix the other template errors.
* Etc
    * Use Result instead of deprecated SimpleResult.
    * Use java.nio.file.NotDirectoryException instead of
      scalax.file.NotDirectoryException.
    * Update README to say use "acvitator" command instead of "play".
    * Add methods to PlayServlet to support Servlet 3.1

IMPORTANT NOTE: You should modify the version of h2database on which
Play depends from 1.3.175 to 1.3.176 in
~/.ivy2/cache/com.typesafe.play/play-jdbc_2.10/ivy-2.3.6.xml as follows:

        <dependency org="com.h2database" name="h2" rev="1.3.176" force="true" conf="compile->compile(*),master(*);runtime->runtime(*)"/>

to avoid org.h2.jdbc.JdbcSQLException because of the bug that h2database
1.3.175 cannot create or alter sequence.

Fixing bad video player on Windows

On Windows native video player was used when user's screen was a touchscreen. I just deleted it and it solved the problem. So for everyone who had this issue, this is probably because you have a touchscreen.
Subtitles are now working fine and showing up (native video player only supports WEBVTT subtitles).

Patch for video.js to prevent mousemove spam

On certain platforms (including node-webkit on Windows7 64-bit it seems) mousemove events are spammed whether or not the mouse has actually moved. This prevents the video player UI from being hidden since it always thinks the user is moving the mouse.

This is a patch for video.js that filter out the false mousemove events. I've already sent it as a PR to the video.js people, but until they make a decision this is a stopgap measure.

I'm not sure what causes it. Someone on StackExchange said that Webkit firing phantom mousemove events might have something to do with preventing a machine going into standby. The odd thing is that it only happens when the cursor is positioned over certain content. For example, events are not fired if the cursor is positioned over the #header element when selecting a movie, but almost anywhere else will result in a constant stream of mousemoves.

The point is, this seems to fix it for now. Ideally, it should be fixed in Webkit (assuming that's where the problem is from).
